CSS has evolved significantly over the years. Modern CSS offers powerful features that make creating beautiful, responsive designs easier than ever.

## CSS Grid Layout

CSS Grid is a two-dimensional layout system that gives you complete control over your layouts:

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 2rem;
}
```

## Flexbox for One-Dimensional Layouts

Flexbox is perfect for arranging items in a single direction:

```css
.flex-container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}
```

## CSS Custom Properties (Variables)

Custom properties make your CSS more maintainable:

```css
:root {
  --primary-color: #3498db;
  --secondary-color: #2ecc71;
}

.button {
  background-color: var(--primary-color);
}
```

These modern techniques will help you create more efficient and maintainable stylesheets.
